{
  "_contract": [
    "Shared query-DSL conformance fixture — the ONE source of truth for DSL matching semantics",
    "across the three implementations: Rust (crates/tesela-core/src/query.rs, consumed by",
    "crates/tesela-core/tests/query_conformance.rs), web TS (web/src/lib/query-language.ts),",
    "and iOS Swift (app/Tesela-iOS/Sources/Data/LocalQueryEngine.swift). Each language runs",
    "every case through its real parser + matcher; drift here = saved views silently differ",
    "per device. Rust is the source of truth — where implementations disagree, fix the",
    "implementation, never the fixture (unless Rust itself changes first).",
    "",
    "Case shape: { name, dsl, block, expect }",
    "  name    — unique snake/kebab id, used as the assertion message.",
    "  dsl     — the query string fed verbatim to the language's parser.",
    "  expect  — whether the block matches. All cases are block-kind (kind:block, the",
    "            grammar default); page-kind matching is out of fixture scope.",
    "",
    "Block shape (language-neutral; adapt to your engine's native block type):",
    "  text        — display text (first line, property lines stripped). Drives text:,",
    "                and is what is:heading derives from.",
    "  tags        — the block's OWN resolved tags (tags:: property values + #tag tokens,",
    "                already merged/deduped). Inherited-ancestor-tag cases are deliberately",
    "                absent — fixture blocks are standalone; leave inherited chains empty.",
    "  properties  — string→string property map (e.g. {\"status\": \"todo\"}). Never",
    "                contains a \"tags\" key (engines pop tags:: out of properties).",
    "  isHeading   — true iff text's first non-whitespace run is 1–6 '#'s followed by",
    "                whitespace (CommonMark heading). MUST stay consistent with text:",
    "                Rust derives it from text and the consumer test asserts the flag",
    "                agrees; TS/Swift may read the flag or derive — assert the same way.",
    "  onDailyPage — true → the containing note id is a canonical YYYY-MM-DD daily id",
    "                (adapters use \"2026-06-10\"); false → a non-date id (\"fixture-note\").",
    "                Drives on:daily-page.",
    "  noteType    — the containing page's note_type, null for plain pages. Drives",
    "                on:system-pages (system = Tag | Property | Query | Template).",
    "",
    "Semantics pinned by these cases (Rust behavior, 2026-06-10):",
    "  * All key/value matching is ASCII-case-insensitive.",
    "  * key:v1,v2 = OR within the key (comma multi-value). Commas must be TIGHT — no",
    "    whitespace on either side; a loose comma ends the list (stray punctuation).",
    "    Comma lists are Eq-only sugar; tag-in:a,b is the back-compat alias for tag:a,b.",
    "  * -clause / negation: -has:k matches absence; -key:v1,v2 = not-any-member;",
    "    missing property matches any negated equality (missing != value).",
    "  * has:k tests property presence regardless of value.",
    "  * Unknown on:/is: values match nothing on Eq, everything on Ne (graceful degrade).",
    "  * key: with an empty value is a dropped clause (query degrades toward match-all).",
    "  * The Inbox default (status:backlog,todo -has:scheduled -has:deadline) is the",
    "    seeded built-in view's DSL — pub const INBOX_VIEW_DSL in query.rs."
  ],
  "cases": [
